The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 August is 67,337 (7,761 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 August, there were 2,486 new confirmed cases (286.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 August, there were 2,577 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (91 fewer cases).
